1. Discovery & Planning
	•	Clarify the business problem
	•	Define user roles and responsibilities
	•	Identify core pain points
	•	Define a strict MVP scope
	•	Explicitly list what is out of scope
⸻
2. System Analysis
	•	Define use cases per role
	•	Describe user flows in text form
	•	Identify critical workflows
	•	Define business rules and constraints
⸻
3. Architecture Design
	•	High-level system architecture
	•	Frontend / Backend responsibilities
	•	API communication strategy (HTTP vs Real-time)
	•	Authentication & authorization model
	•	Database modeling approach
⸻
4. Tech Stack Validation
	•	Validate framework and tool versions
	•	Prefer stable, well-documented releases
	•	Recommend downgrades if stability is a concern
	•	Justify every major technology choice
⸻
5. Domain & Data Design
	•	Define core domain entities
	•	Define relationships and ownership
	•	Design order / shipment status lifecycle
	•	Identify domain events and side effects
⸻
6. API Design
	•	Design RESTful endpoints
	•	Define DTOs and validation rules
	•	Standardize error handling
	•	Define security boundaries
⸻
7. Frontend Strategy
	•	Define layout and navigation structure
	•	Role-based access control
	•	State management boundaries
	•	UX flows for dashboards and forms
⸻
8. Incremental Implementation
	•	Implement features incrementally
	•	Complete and validate one feature before starting another
	•	Review code quality and architecture continuously

⸻
9. Stability & Readiness
•	Identify edge cases and failure scenarios
	•	Define basic testing strategy
	•	Ensure production readiness (logging, configs, security)